cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the process of discovering and reusing data for research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization and retrieval of digital information. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it focuses on finding and analyzing information. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the study aims to inform the design of community-centric solutions and policies. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper probes the role of social interactions in data discovery. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is relevant as the study may involve sensitive data and the need for secure data sharing practices.
